   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">With Arawan going up first, you can go through your deck and choose whatever you want.  All the creatures in the deck have dreamwarp except for the 2 treepish.  Play the Robe and play a few creatures (u used the power of Arawan on your first power/spell/relic stage).  i normally go get a river abaquist.  I play like 4 creatures, then throw a river abaquist for 1 energy (dreamwarp down, and then the petals kick in).  Take a creature.  Now they really have to extend their resources on the first magi to regain a fair position.  Keep goin throught the deck every turn untill Arawan dies.<br>
<br>
When Ookami comes into the field, you should have a decent hand.  With the drums, and possibly the staff of vines.  Play the drums, the creatures you need, and maybe the staff of vines, and if your lucky bagala fangs.  You can gain MASSIVE energy with these cards.  First, play the drums and the staff of vines, then play 3-4 creatures.  The hardshell weebo should be dreamwarped up one.  From the staff take an energy from the weebo and add it to whatever (2 energy!).  now use the drums to pump the weebo up to 3.  Of course use the lahalou power, and then the vine power on all the creatures.  You should have the control at this point. <br>
<br>
Kioko is very powerful, especially as a follow up to ookami.  You will most likely have a spell pulse and several creatures.  you will swamp your opponent no problem.  USE THE FANGS WISELY! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
